<section class="section type-section-padding-bottom">
    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="title title--h2">Top 10 Tips To Win More At Slots</h1>
        <p>
            All online slot games use something called a <a href="/guides/random-number-generators" class="text--link">Random Number Generator (RNG)</a> that determines the results of each spin. What this means for you, the player, is that slot machine games are purely games of luck. There is no guarantee that your spin will be a winner. Even a game with a 98% payout percentage is based on an average payout and doesn't mean that any specific spin of yours be a winner.
        </p>
        <p>
            However, there are still a number of important tips for online slots that will help you improve your playing experience and get more enjoyment out of your game play. In fact, 10 tips weren't enough so we threw in one extra! And yes, there are even tips to help you increase your chances of winning big!
        </p>
        <h2 class="title title--h2"><span class="title__number">1</span>  Play For Free To Test The Waters</h2>
        <p>
            Many online slot games have <a href="/free" class="text--link">free versions</a> or online demos that you can try out before you commit money to your play. Internet casinos have their terms of service that describe the types of welcome bonuses they offer and may even post the payout percentages of their games. Reputable casinos will also detail how they handle security and whom they work with to independently verify that their RNG is reliable. Look around and make an informed decision before you deposit funds.
        </p>
        <h2 class="title title--h2"><span class="title__number">2</span>  Don't Waste Time With Boring Slots Games</h2>
        <p>
            The best slot machine game for you depends upon the type of experience you are looking for. Since Internet slots come in a variety of styles and vary in terms of the type of payout they offer, think about your goals before you play. Some slot games are cinematic masterpieces, offering blockbuster quality graphics (some in 3D) and sound. Other games may be less like a movie experience but may have a payout table that matches your gambling style.
        </p>
        <h2 class="title title--h2"><span class="title__number">3</span>  Study The Paylines To Know Your Payouts</h2>
        <p>
            Remember that online slots games differ in the number of paylines they offer. Some have only a small number while others can have hundreds. Games where you can play more paylines offer you more chances to win per spin. Some <a href="/guides/slot-machine-history" class="text--link">Internet slot machines</a> have special prizes when you play a certain payline or offer jackpots if you play the maximum number of paylines. In general, it is a good idea to look for a large number of paylines and play the maximum number of paylines possible to maximize your chances of winning.
        </p>
        <p>
            Remember that the payout is based upon having winning combinations of symbols (from left to right) on only the paylines you have selected (active paylines). Your enjoyment of the game may be reduced if you spin and see an unattainable payout because it is on a payline that you didn't activate.
        </p>
        <h2 class="title title--h2"><span class="title__number">4</span>  Understand Progressive Jackpots And How To Play For Them</h2>
        <p>
            Some online slot games offer jackpot prize pools. A non-progressive or stand-alone jackpot is one where the jackpot is based upon play at that specific online slot machine. The prize is fixed and does not vary. A <a href="/progressive-jackpots" class="text--link">progressive jackpot</a> slot game is linked to a network of players spinning slots at multiple Internet casinos.
        </p>
        <p>
            In both cases, each time you bet and spin, a portion of that bet is added to the jackpot. If you win the jackpot pool, the amount of money won can be big and even a life-changing sum of money. Here, the amount you can win is based upon the total number of bets that have been added to the prize pool and can vary. The jackpot is usually triggered by hitting a specified combination of the highest paying symbols.
        </p>
        <h2 class="title title--h2"><span class="title__number">5</span>  Large jackpot prizes are designed to be hard to win.</h2>
        <p>
            There are generally specific conditions that must be met in order for you to win the jackpot. Usually you must play the maximum number of paylines and be betting the maximum value and amount of coins possible in order to be eligible for the jackpot prize.
        </p>
        <p>
            Don't forget that there is a RNG working behind the scenes. Just because a jackpot hasn't been won in a long time doesn't mean that it is "due" to hit. Generally, lower jackpot slot games will hit the jackpot more often than higher jackpot games.
        </p>
        <h2 class="title title--h2"><span class="title__number">6</span>  Pay Attention To How Many Symbols A Game Has</h2>
        <p>
            Check out how many different symbols an online slot game has. The more symbols it has, the more possible combinations each spin will have. The upside is that there will likely be more special symbols that equal larger payouts. However, the downside is that the more symbols available in a slot machine, the less likely you'll hit multiples of any given symbol.
        </p>
        <h2 class="title title--h2"><span class="title__number">7</span> Learn The Rules Specific To A Game</h2>
        <p>
            It is important to check out the rules of the online slot game you're playing and make sure you understand if there are any special rules involved. For example, certain prizes may be possible only when you bet the maximum number of coins and play the maximum number of paylines. Another example involves the behaviour of wildcard symbols that differ from one game to the next. Know what combinations trigger bonus games or free spins.
        </p>
        <h2 class="title title--h2"><span class="title__number">8</span>  Choose A Comfortable Coin Size</h2>
        <p>
            Online slot games usually offer a range of coin denominations that can be used per line/per spin. If a game takes bets between 1 and 25 coins, and has 100 paylines, your spin can cost anywhere from 1 coin (playing only one payline for the minimum bet) up to 2,500 coins (maximum bet over the maximum number of paylines).
        </p>

        <div class="quote-block">
