            <div>Depending upon your bankroll for playing slots online, you could play all day or lose your entire roll within one spin! So think about how much money you have set aside for playing and calculate how often you want to spin for the maximum bet and largest number of paylines. Then pick a slot game that will let you get the maximum amount of play time for your budget.</div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="title title--h2"><span class="title__number">9</span>  Don't Gamble What You Cannot Afford To Lose</h2>
        <p>
            Online slot games are pure chance and pure gambling. There is never a guarantee that you will win at the game. You should always have a clear idea of the amount of money you are willing to lose and only play with that amount. Set a playing budget and stick to it always.
        </p>
        <p>
            It is easy to be tempted to redeposit and keep playing after you have lost your entire bankroll in order to "win it back." But this is a strategy that is highly discouraged. Gambling (online or otherwise) is entertainment until you start playing with money that you can't afford to lose. Know your limits and stop when you have hit them.
        </p>
        <h2 class="title title--h2"><span class="title__number">10</span> Grab Those Online Casino Bonuses</h2>
        <p>
            Many online casinos will offer <a href="/guides/welcome-bonus" class="text--link">welcome bonuses</a> to new players and to players making subsequent deposits of funds. These bonuses can double your initial bankroll. Know the rules and make sure to maximizes the playing power of your deposit.
        </p>
        <p>
            Make sure you understand what you have to do in order to release the extra money and be able to cash it out. Casinos may offer reward programs for certain volumes of play. Understand what the casino is offering to win your loyalty and continued play and take advantage of these offers as best as you can.
        </p>
        <h2 class="title title--h2"><span class="title__number">11</span>  Understand That Slots Is A Game Of Luck</h2>
        <p>
            You may hear many strategy tips for winning at slot games. While there are definitely strategies for maximising your potential wins, there is no guaranteed way to know that any given spin will be a winner.
        </p>
        <p>
            A game is never "hot" or "cold." The RNG determines that each spin has exactly the same chance of hitting a winning combination as any other spin. This also means that a long stretch of no hits is completely unrelated to whether your next spin will be a winner or not.
        </p>
